comp3111.data.model

Class PromoEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • comp3111.data.model.PromoEvent

  • @Entity
public class PromoEvent
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a promo event associated with an offering. Automatically triggers at getTriggerDate(), and will send out a custom message to all known customers.

      • PromoEvent

        public PromoEvent(java.util.Date triggerDate,
                  java.lang.String customMessage,
                  java.lang.String promoCode,
                  double discount,
                  int promoCodeUsesLeft,
                  int maxReservationsPerCustomer,
                  Offering offering)
        Constructs a transient PromoEvent object.
        Parameters:
        triggerDate - The date and time at which the promotional message will be broadcasted to all customers
        customMessage - A custom message to be sent to everyone
        promoCode - A promo code which can be used to make a booking at a discount price
        discount - A double between [0, 1.0] indicating the discount amount. E.g. 1.0 for full price (no discount)
        promoCodeUsesLeft - How many times this promo code may be used
        maxReservationsPerCustomer - The maximum number of spots each customer may reserve when making a booking (i.e. Booking.getTotalNumberOfPeople() can be at most this value)
        offering - The offering for which this promo code can be used to make bookings for
